#### Issue details
I tried to build an auto scrolling TextArea (for an in-game log) based on [this snippet](https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/3796#issuecomment-202729107). But when text is added consecutively, the TextArea removes the first line instead of just growing, so that the outer ScrollPane can do its magic.

A simple workaround, was to just add 1 to the value returned by `getLines()`, but I don't like magic numbers and I think there's something wrong in the way the backing `lineBreaks` array is maintained.
I tried calling `calculateOffsets()` before the call of `getLines()`, but that didn't help.

